### Test JWT Authentication Endpoints
@token = 'Hello'
@hostAddress = http://localhost:5184

### 1. Login with admin user (admin user is defined in server/database seed data; verify in seed file or database)
POST {{hostAddress}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "username": "admin",
    "password": "admin123"
}

> {%
client.global.set("token", response.body.token);
%}

### 2. Get current user info (requires token from login)
GET {{hostAddress}}/api/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 3. Try to access protected products endpoint without token (should fail)
GET {{hostAddress}}/api/products

### 4. Try to access protected products endpoint with token (should work)
GET {{hostAddress}}/api/products
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 5. Try to access protected inventory endpoint with token
GET {{hostAddress}}/api/inventory
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 6. Create a new product (protected endpoint)
POST {{hostAddress}}/api/products
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "Test Product JWT",
    "description": "Product created via JWT authenticated request",
    "price": 29.99,
    "quantity": 100,
    "category": "Electronics"
}
